		<content type="html" xml:base="http://skysedge.us/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1485&amp;p=1526#p1526"><![CDATA[
Just wrote a simple sketch to test the USB serial hardware, it works, MegaCore is fine:<div class="codebox"><p>CODE: </p><pre><code>// Toggle the Status &amp; Hook LEDs// while sending test strings over USB serial// Define general output pinsconst byte StatusLED = 13;const byte HookLED = 49;bool toggle = 1;int  count = 1;void setup(){// Set output pin functions  pinMode(StatusLED, OUTPUT);  pinMode(HookLED, OUTPUT);  Serial.begin(9600);}void loop() {  // put your main code here, to run repeatedly:  digitalWrite(HookLED, toggle);  digitalWrite(StatusLED, !toggle);  Serial.print("USB serial: ");  Serial.println(count);  toggle = !toggle;  count++;  delay(500);}</code></pre></div>This toggles some LEDs while sending text over the USB serial, it works. USB serial should be useful for debugging but for some strange reason I'm not receiving USB serial using Justine's code. I've probably done something stupid.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://skysedge.us/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1724">SteveC</a> — Sun Apr 26, 2020 1:55 am</p><hr />
